{"type":"text","timestamp":1775845459475,"sessionID":"ses_287604f96ffeaki2IdoYVkEile","part":{"id":"prt_d78a3371600127CGBoz21wexga","messageID":"msg_d78a32d1b00186tDYHc4qhjbgT","sessionID":"ses_287604f96ffeaki2IdoYVkEile","type":"text","text":"All tests pass with race detection and good coverage. The AR-006 implementation is complete:\n\n**Implemented Components:**\n\n1. **Sandbox Deletion Handler** (`handler/sandbox.go`)\n   - `HandleDeleteSandbox` - HTTP endpoint for manual sandbox deletion\n   - Supports both Sandbox and SandboxClaim resources\n   - Proper error handling for not found and internal errors\n\n2. **Sandbox Deletion Controller** (`controller/sandbox.go`)\n   - `DeleteSession` - Core deletion logic\n   - Deletes Kubernetes resources and removes from store\n   - Handles cases where K8s resources may not exist\n\n3. **Garbage Collector** (`garbage_collector.go`)\n   - `GarbageCollector` - Automatic cleanup of idle and expired sandboxes\n   - Configurable interval (default 15s)\n   - Cleanup audit logging with reason tracking\n   - Supports both idle timeout and expired cleanup reasons\n\n4. **Cleanup Types** (`types/sandbox_types.go`)\n   - `SandboxCleanupReason` - Enum for cleanup reasons (manual, idle_timeout, expired)\n   - `CleanupAuditEntry` - Audit log entry structure\n\n5. **Complete Test Coverage** (87%+ coverage)\n   - Controller tests for deletion\n   - Handler tests for HTTP endpoints\n   - Garbage collector tests for automatic cleanup\n   - Error scenario handling\n\n**Test Results:**\n- ✅ All 20+ tests pass\n- ✅ No race conditions\n- ✅ 87%+ code coverage\n- ✅ Proper error handling verified","time":{"start":1775845459472,"end":1775845459472}}}
